Political Capital: The Hungarian Guard has increased the risk country
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital (Risk Analysis Division), the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed last August, with the support of the Jobbik Magyarországért Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary) increases the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its "risk warning", society notes that, in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that "in the short term aggressive ethnic confrontations may occur as a result of the worsening ethnic tension already existing between the Gypsy and non-Hungarian population of Hungary."
The research institute has added that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy likely to cause this situation is the main reason.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of the Hungarian political actors: "public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of radical and extreme political groupings that have based a political strategy on the dispute between the Gypsies and the Hungarians."
The problem is aggravated, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and aggressive conflicts are more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, with the effect of increasing attention from the Hungarian and international media, the activity of the Hungarian Guard "has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, in particular concerning confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country".
They recall that, following a greater publicity given to the reorganization of the Hungarian radical and extreme right groups since the fall of 2006, many associations have been formed in Hungary since the summer of 2007 as "national self-defence association".
"The common feature of these gatherings is that they define themselves as a civil organization when they publicly declare the preparation of their members to defence missions (catastrophes, national defence, defence of order), armed if necessary, in addition, by referring to the inability of the police, the army, in other words the state," they added.
They noted that everything was done according to the method that, based on the political society and party rancour, seeks to disguise different political ambitions in a civil way.
