In Hungary, the law defines exactly the holiday days and, around the holidays, it has become common to reorganize the working days whose number will decrease next year.
Parties are not uniform in the EU and the United States either.
Hungarian legislation distinguishes national and state holidays and rest days.
Rest days are often linked to religious festivals or important historical events.
In Hungary, we celebrate the new year, the last day of the year ending and the first day of the new year are also days of rest, especially so that the awakenings can rest quietly.
On the other hand, in a year, we have eleven red parties.
March 15 is a national festival, commemorating the revolution of 1848, as on October 23rd also that is the memorial day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrate the constitution of our state, on May 1 is the work party and on November 1 and 2, we remember our family members and our dead friends.
In addition, we have two days at Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
The days of our state, national or even religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, according to the calendar, it has become common to reorganize working days in cases or there remains only one working day before or after the party marked in red.
It is true that we pay the price of extended weekends by working or going to school on Saturday before the extended weekend.
For many years, the Minister of Labour has ruled in particular on days of replacement of the days before or after the holidays.
The Act extends to all employers and their employees, civil servants and persons working in the public service.
It does not, however, apply to service companies, institutions operating continuously and in service, through their vocation, and also for rest days.
This year, working days will be modified only around the end of the year's holidays: from December 24, life stops almost throughout the country because according to the experiences most people do rather overtime hours or take vacations they have saved for these purposes in order to spend the days between Christmas and the day of the new year at their home.
The next year, many parties fall in the middle or end of the week, so there will be fewer changes in working days compared to this year.
The calendar will be reorganized the first time around the work party to allow employees to stay at home for four days.
Saturday, April 25 will be a day of work to have a day of rest on Friday, May 2.
Another change is scheduled for 23 October: Saturday 18 October will be a working day replacing Friday 24.
On the other hand, next year, the end of the year is announced under the sign of the holidays because from December 24, everyone will take a non-stop break even if the new year's day falls on a Wednesday.
