What assurance do I need?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible claims, implies a significant expenditure that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of driving licence, marital status, the type of vehicle to be ensured or the use in fact, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance is even harder than choosing the vehicle model.
And it is that choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange it becomes liable for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of an accident.
The premium is the insurance price, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be ensured or the actual use, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the more likely an accident is, the higher the rate to be paid.
That is why people over the age of 25 and women must pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower rate of claims than they are careful.
Similarly, using censuses, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and thus the probability of an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when establishing the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must carefully study the situation to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the insurer's characteristics, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 are faced with various drawbacks when a contract is made with insurance at an accessible price, as can be the low driving experience and the old driving licence.
Although the ideal to be well-secured is insurance at all risk, other more economical options exist.
The most likely drivers can opt for insurance at any risk honestly, so that they obtain coverage from insurance at any risk but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the client pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the claim that the customer pays will be determined according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be lower," states Luis Noguera, the responsible in Spain of First Europe, online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
A tip.
If you are under 25 years of age, try to be cautious and avoid the damage to the extent possible, since this will affect the bonus, which may reduce the insurance price in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the company's base rate.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
"The subsidies and sanctions will depend on the company and the profit of the company.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to increase the bonus," Noguera clarifies.
Beyond the age of 25 this becomes easier for drivers when entering into a contract with insurance, as the rate of claims is reduced thanks to accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is preferable to choose insurance at all risk honestly.
"Usually young people cannot take advantage of the experience previously acquired after an accident," says the European company manager in Spain, adding that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'novice fear' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not have children yet it is preferable for him to negotiate insurance at any risk, since his economic situation allows him.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers as people with the lowest rate of claims, because increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance at all risk with free (may be EUR 300), or insurance to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have a more relaxed drive and they have greater purchasing power to allow themselves the luxury to assume a greater amount of franchises," says Luis Noguera.
In the case of pensioners, insurance at all risk with free will is preferable (in the case of EUR 150), or extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of subsidy.
It must be said that motor insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible claims, but also because it represents an important expense, that is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
